%S A395815 1,8,1728,1728000,4741632000,27653197824000,294451250429952000,
%T A395815 5175275177556836352000,139732429794034581504000000,
%U A395815 5492043420624735191433216000000,301359406576520469424323428352000000,22327115714441248538709274159742976000000
%N A395815 Number of perfect matchings in the complete tripartite graph K_{2n,2n,2n}.
%C A395815 A perfect matching exists only when the number of vertices 3n is even, so a(n) = 0 for odd n.
%C A395815 a(k) = A001813(k)^3, the cube of the quadruple factorial (2k)!/k!.
%C A395815 The number of perfect matchings of the complete multipartite graph K_{n_1,...,n_r} equals E[Product_i He_{n_i}(X)] with X a standard normal random variable, where He is the probabilists' Hermite polynomial (see Azor, Gillis and Victor). Here a(n) = E[He_{2n}(X)^3].
%D A395815 R. Azor, J. Gillis and J. Victor, Combinatorial applications of Hermite polynomials, SIAM Journal on Mathematical Analysis, 13 (1982), 879-890.
%H A395815 Meghanto Majumder, <a href="/A395815/b395815.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..142</a>
%H A395815 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CompleteTripartiteGraph.html">Complete Tripartite Graph</a>.
%H A395815 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/PerfectMatching.html">Perfect Matching</a>.
%F A395815 a(n) = ((2n)!/n!)^3 = A001813(n)^3.
%F A395815 a(n) = n!^3 * binomial(2n, n)^3.
%F A395815 a(n) = 8*(2n-1)^3 * a(n-1) for n >= 1.
%F A395815 a(n) = (2*Pi)^(-1/2) * Integral_{x=-oo..oo} He_{2n}(x)^3 * exp(-x^2/2) dx, where He_n is the probabilists' Hermite polynomial.
%e A395815 a(1) = 8: K_{2,2,2} is the octahedron graph, which has 8 perfect matchings.
%t A395815 a[n_] := (n!)^3*Binomial[2n, n]^3; Array[a, 12, 0]
%o A395815 (PARI) a(n) = (n!*binomial(2*n, n))^3;
%o A395815 (Python)
%o A395815 from math import factorial, comb
%o A395815 def a(n): return (factorial(n)*comb(2*n, n))**3
%Y A395815 Cf. A000142 (perfect matchings of K_{n,n}), A002720 (matchings of K_{n,n}), A293075 (matchings of K_{n,n,n}), A297487 (maximal matchings of K_{n,n,n}), A395813 (perfect matchings of K_{n,n,n,n}).
%Y A395815 Cf. A001813.
%K A395815 nonn,easy,new
%O A395815 0,2
